03></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Electrical Question...</span><hr size=1> Okay I don't know the first thing about wiring and electrical stuff.. But I'm hoping some of you do. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Here's the situation.. I hooked up my home theater system a couple nights back. Now in the same room as my home theater, I have a mini-refrigerator. They are not plugged into the same outlet or anything but the 2 outlets they are plugged into are in the same room. Now you know how a fridge will keep turning on and off to regulate the temperature? Well everytime the fridge turns off, the speakers in my home theater pop.. It's really getting annoying to be watching a movie and then all of a sudden... POP! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  So does anyone have any idea what could be causing this and more importantly what I can do to fix it? Any help would be appreciated. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Thanks guys! <p><br><p><img alt="Sig Pic" src="http://people.mn.mediaone.net/timelord81/images/web2.jpg">
